       <span width="0.25em" class="mspace"/>
      </div>
      <graphic xlink:href="11356_2018_1859_Article_Equ6.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </disp-formula>illustrating that for scenarios when 
    <div id="IEq5" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
     <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
      <tex-math id="M27" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {c}_0&gt;\overline{W}/Q\left(1+K{t}_d\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M28" display="inline" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">c</span>
        <span class="mn">0</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">&gt;</span>
       <div accent="true" class="mover">
        <span class="mi">W</span>
        <span stretchy="true" class="mo">¯</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">/</span>
       <span class="mi">Q</span>
       <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mn">1</span>
         <span class="mo">+</span>
         <span class="mi">K</span>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">t</span>
          <span class="mi">d</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span xlink:href="11356_2018_1859_Article_IEq5.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </div> concentration in the aquifer will progressively decrease as the step input is not large enough to increase the overall aquifer concentration and at large times will achieve the equilibrium value, 
    <div id="IEq6" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
     <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
      <tex-math id="M29" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \overline{W}/Q\left(1+K{t}_d\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M30" display="inline" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div accent="true" class="mover">
        <span class="mi">W</span>
        <span stretchy="true" class="mo">¯</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">/</span>
       <span class="mi">Q</span>
       <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mn">1</span>
         <span class="mo">+</span>
         <span class="mi">K</span>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">t</span>
          <span class="mi">d</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span xlink:href="11356_2018_1859_Article_IEq6.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </div>. Otherwise, when 
    <div id="IEq7" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
     <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
      <tex-math id="M31" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {c}_0&lt;\overline{W}/Q\left(1+K{t}_d\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M32" display="inline" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">c</span>
        <span class="mn">0</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">&lt;</span>
       <div accent="true" class="mover">
        <span class="mi">W</span>
        <span stretchy="true" class="mo">¯</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">/</span>
       <span class="mi">Q</span>
       <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mn">1</span>
         <span class="mo">+</span>
         <span class="mi">K</span>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">t</span>
          <span class="mi">d</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span xlink:href="11356_2018_1859_Article_IEq7.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </div>, concentration in the aquifer will continuously buildup until the equilibrium concentration is reached.
   </p>
   <p id="Par74" class="p">In the analysis of climate change effects, recharge reductions will affect the 
    <italic class="italic">Q</italic> term, while fertilizer management and control will relate to the 
    <div id="IEq8" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
